    Multinomial: n>p Benchmarks

    Akarsh Goyal

    2020-08-30

    multinomial.Rmd
    library(solvers)

    Well Conditioned Problems

    n > p

    set.seed(34)
d <- randomProblem(11, 1,  response="multinomial", density = 1, rho=0)
f <- getBenchmarks(d$x, d$y, family="multinomial", path_length = 100)
